The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, visited the Erbil Air Base in Iraqi Kurdistan to express gratitude to the American military personnel stationed there. He thanked them for their service and sacrifice in defending the nation and fighting against terrorism. Pence also acknowledged the hardships faced by the servicemen and their families, especially during the Thanksgiving holiday. He highlighted the progress made in the fight against ISIS and the successful operation that led to the death of ISIS leader Abu Bakr al-Baghdadi. Pence assured the troops that the Trump administration is committed to strengthening the military and providing the necessary resources and support. He concluded by expressing his gratitude and wishing them a happy Thanksgiving.